comment.body:
@macumber : Correct about the (culprit) edge. My initial [comments](https://github.com/rd2/osut/pull/15#discussion_r1367737674) may be somewhat obscure, but I point this out in the very last paragraph:

> If one were to comment out the final vertex addition of all 3 sets of extra wrapping vertices (e.g. vtx << mini_floor_vtx[3] # ?), then OpenStudio v3.7.0-rc1 will not log to stdout the aforementioned unenclosed polyhedron messages. However, neither OpenStudio nor EnergyPlus will then report the correct floor areas and volumes. As with previous EnergyPlus runs, there are no reported warnings or errors with this slightly-altered solution. The initial solution is obviously preferred.

There's a brief paragraph on this [here](https://github.com/rd2/osut/blob/63719558293794ee569f79d78e16bc1ad11817f1/spec/osut_tests_spec.rb#L2905). So one could comment out the following 3 lines ([here](https://github.com/rd2/osut/blob/63719558293794ee569f79d78e16bc1ad11817f1/spec/osut_tests_spec.rb#L2920), [here](https://github.com/rd2/osut/blob/63719558293794ee569f79d78e16bc1ad11817f1/spec/osut_tests_spec.rb#L2930) and [here](https://github.com/rd2/osut/blob/63719558293794ee569f79d78e16bc1ad11817f1/spec/osut_tests_spec.rb#L2940)) and rerun (`bundle exec rake`) with v3.7.0-rc1: polyhedron messages would no longer flash to stdout. Not a good long term solution, but it isolates the issue.
